name: Baked Macaroni and Cheese
prepTime: 45 minutes
cookTime: 30 minutes
bakingTemperature: 350
portions: 8

ingredients:
  - (8 tb) unsalted butter
  - (1/2 cup) flour
  - (4 cups) milk
  - ( ) salt, pepper, nutmeg, chives
  - (4 tsp) sherry
  - (2.5) onions
  - (1/2 tsp) sweet paprika
  - (2) bay leaves
  - (1 lb) cellentani noodles
  - (1/2 lb) white cheddar cheese
  - (1/4 lb) swiss cheese
  - (1/4 lb) jarlsberg cheese
  - (1) habenero
  - ( ) breadcrumbs
 
steps:
  - Preheat oven to 350
  - Melt butter over medium low heat in a medium sized dutch oven
  - Whisk in butter gradually, and heat until thick and smooth (about 1 minute). Make sure to whisk constantly, to prevent lumps
  - Remove the roux from the heat, and whish in the milk gradually
  - Return to the heat, and raise to medium
  - Bring to a simmer, whisking constantly to keep smooth (about 20 minutes)
  - Once thick and smooth, add salt, pepper, and nutmeg to taste (I recommend about 1tsp each), and also
    sherry, chives, onions, paprika, bay leaves, and habenero
  - Bring to a simmer, and cook covered voer low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally
  - Meanwhile, cook cellentani according to package
  - Grate cheeses, and mix together in a large mixing bowl
  - Add 2/3 cheese to the sauce, and add salt and pepper to taste
  - Drain the noodles, and mix with sauce
  - Add half the mixter to a 9 x 13 baking tray, then sprinkle half the remaining heese on top
  - Add the remaining mixture, top with remaining cheese, and sprinkle with bread crumbs
  - Bake for 30 minutes. Let cool 5 minutes before seving.
